1
00:00:07,018 --> 00:00:11,455
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,523 --> 00:00:15,050
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:15,126 --> 00:00:18,562
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,630 --> 00:00:22,225
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:25,565
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,637 --> 00:00:27,571
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,374 --> 00:00:32,309
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,377 --> 00:00:36,177
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,581 --> 00:00:43,419
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,655 --> 00:00:50,720
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:51,029 --> 00:00:57,161
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,302 --> 00:01:01,568
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:05,235
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,310 --> 00:01:08,643
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,713 --> 00:01:12,342
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,417 --> 00:01:16,012
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:16,087 --> 00:01:19,579
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,658 --> 00:01:23,116
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,328 --> 00:01:27,424
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:39,188 --> 00:01:41,884
What should we do, Aoi?

21
00:01:42,424 --> 00:01:44,483
I'll go with Fukusuke.

22
00:01:45,294 --> 00:01:47,194
You go after Idate.

23
00:01:47,429 --> 00:01:48,396
- Right!
- Right!

24
00:01:50,366 --> 00:01:53,802
Hey, Idate!
The ocean is that way!

25
00:01:53,936 --> 00:01:56,734
Where are you going!
Come back!

26
00:01:57,272 --> 00:01:59,240
Hah! There's no way
I'm going back!

27
00:02:09,184 --> 00:02:09,775
Let's go

28
00:02:10,352 --> 00:02:10,943
Right!

29
00:02:14,957 --> 00:02:17,425
<i>What does that kid think</i>
<i>he's doing?</i>

30
00:02:18,327 --> 00:02:20,887
Looks like he's run away.

31
00:02:21,563 --> 00:02:24,157
Idate's been like that
from long ago.

32
00:02:24,566 --> 00:02:25,498
You know him?

33
00:02:25,968 --> 00:02:27,367
Yes, kind of...

34
00:02:34,276 --> 00:02:40,215
<i>The Race is On!</i>
<i>Trouble on the High Seas!</i>

35
00:02:43,652 --> 00:02:45,916
I knew he'd run away,
that bastard Idate.

36
00:02:46,588 --> 00:02:49,989
Knowing him this long
you must've figured this would happen.

37
00:02:50,359 --> 00:02:52,793
It was a mistake to let him run!

38
00:02:53,495 --> 00:02:56,521
You idiots!
Idate isn't that kind of kid!

39
00:02:56,999 --> 00:02:57,727
- Boss!
- Boss...

40
00:02:58,333 --> 00:03:00,028
I believe in Idate.

41
00:03:01,136 --> 00:03:03,434
He must have a plan.

42
00:03:04,873 --> 00:03:05,805
Jirocho!

43
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:07,671
Chief Retainer!

44
00:03:08,610 --> 00:03:11,135
How do you think
you're going to settle this?

45
00:03:14,450 --> 00:03:18,250
You've turned this grand traditional
festival into a mere farce...

46
00:03:18,754 --> 00:03:20,984
And worse,
in the presence of the lord!

47
00:03:21,623 --> 00:03:27,926
Sir, the race has just begun.
Please watch it until the end.

48
00:03:34,203 --> 00:03:39,004
Since you insist that much,
you had better win.

49
00:03:39,908 --> 00:03:41,569
If you lose...

50
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:47,677
I'll ask for the dissolution
of your family!

51
00:03:48,450 --> 00:03:50,941
Agreed! I'm a man of my word.

52
00:03:51,286 --> 00:03:55,746
If Idate loses,
you may do anything you wish.

53
00:03:58,994 --> 00:04:03,090
How like Wasabi's Jirocho.
Such confidence.

54
00:04:03,799 --> 00:04:05,767
Don't let us down.

55
00:04:09,538 --> 00:04:11,529
<i>I'm counting on you, Idate.</i>

56
00:04:18,347 --> 00:04:19,006
Boss...

57
00:04:22,151 --> 00:04:23,049
Give me your money!

58
00:04:31,193 --> 00:04:32,421
Just be still!

59
00:04:32,828 --> 00:04:34,955
A starving thief, huh...

60
00:04:35,364 --> 00:04:36,888
Sh-Shut up!

61
00:04:41,303 --> 00:04:42,861
A kid trying to act tough!

62
00:04:46,909 --> 00:04:48,001
With that little thing,

63
00:04:48,076 --> 00:04:49,407
you can't even peel an apple,
can you?!

64
00:04:49,912 --> 00:04:50,401
Here!

65
00:04:57,019 --> 00:04:57,644
Take this.

66
00:04:59,121 --> 00:05:02,682
Edged tools aren't
for hurting people.

67
00:05:07,296 --> 00:05:09,161
You don't have anywhere to go,
do you?

68
00:05:12,234 --> 00:05:15,795
I'm Jirocho of Wasabi
of Degarashi Port.

69
00:05:16,471 --> 00:05:18,803
Wasabi... Jirocho?

70
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:21,532
How about it?
Why don't you come to my place?

71
00:05:23,645 --> 00:05:25,772
I-I just tried to...

72
00:05:26,515 --> 00:05:29,814
Anyone on the verge of starvation
will make such mistakes...

73
00:05:30,852 --> 00:05:31,819
I don't hold it against you.

74
00:05:35,891 --> 00:05:36,949
Ah... this...

75
00:05:37,092 --> 00:05:40,550
I gave it to you.
Keep it.

76
00:05:41,763 --> 00:05:45,164
Don't ever do stupid things
like stealing...

77
00:05:48,904 --> 00:05:50,235
M-Mister!

78
00:05:51,473 --> 00:05:53,805
Listen!
Make me your henchman!

79
00:05:54,443 --> 00:05:56,536
No, I mean...
could you please, Boss!

80
00:05:58,747 --> 00:05:59,577
What's your name?

81
00:05:59,848 --> 00:06:02,112
Idate...
My name is Idate Morino.

82
00:06:08,757 --> 00:06:10,782
Shall we go then, Idate?

83
00:06:12,961 --> 00:06:16,158
<i>Boss, just trust in me!</i>
<i>I will win, no matter what!</i>

84
00:06:22,804 --> 00:06:24,635
We can catch up
to him in a bit!

85
00:06:24,906 --> 00:06:26,237
But it's too late now!

86
00:06:26,475 --> 00:06:28,909
He can't win if
he's this far from the port!

87
00:06:29,244 --> 00:06:33,180
No, he may've planned to come
this way from the very beginning

88
00:06:33,415 --> 00:06:33,972
What?

89
00:06:34,916 --> 00:06:35,541
Huh?

90
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:50,261
How lucky!

91
00:06:51,633 --> 00:06:53,726
Now, we can stop them here.

92
00:06:57,806 --> 00:06:59,103
At any rate...

93
00:06:59,608 --> 00:07:02,736
who would've thought
they'd be escorting him.

94
00:07:03,245 --> 00:07:07,272
Double Lucky!
Now I can pay them back.

95
00:07:10,585 --> 00:07:12,212
For what they did to us
during the Chunin Exams.

96
00:07:14,790 --> 00:07:18,248
You two go ahead.
I'll keep them here.

97
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:19,226
All right!

98
00:07:22,331 --> 00:07:24,162
Finally, we've caught up to you!

99
00:07:24,466 --> 00:07:25,728
Hey, wait!

100
00:07:26,368 --> 00:07:28,666
Geez! Why on earth
did you come this way?!

101
00:07:29,037 --> 00:07:31,335
Shut up!
It's none of your business!

102
00:07:31,406 --> 00:07:33,465
What kinda attitude is that?!

103
00:07:33,542 --> 00:07:34,770
I said to shut up!

104
00:07:39,047 --> 00:07:39,911
Watch out!

105
00:07:40,549 --> 00:07:42,380
They aren't aware of it, are they?

106
00:07:42,784 --> 00:07:43,614
Of Genjutsu?

107
00:07:43,885 --> 00:07:45,682
Hey, I said wait up!

108
00:07:48,156 --> 00:07:49,316
I've already been here?

109
00:07:49,691 --> 00:07:52,683
Darn! Looks like
I've been tricked by Genjutsu.

110
00:07:54,296 --> 00:07:55,058
Wha?!

111
00:07:55,230 --> 00:07:56,128
If that's the case...

112
00:07:58,367 --> 00:07:59,026
<i>Release!</i>

113
00:08:04,339 --> 00:08:04,998
<i>There!</i>

114
00:08:05,674 --> 00:08:06,572
H-Hey!

115
00:08:06,641 --> 00:08:08,108
No! Don't go that way!

116
00:08:11,613 --> 00:08:13,706
Huh? What's going on?

117
00:08:18,587 --> 00:08:19,952
I'm out of it!

118
00:08:27,496 --> 00:08:28,656
Just be still!

119
00:08:29,431 --> 00:08:31,228
We'll get pulled up now!

120
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,395
That was close...

121
00:08:34,069 --> 00:08:36,299
A double Genjutsu.

122
00:08:37,239 --> 00:08:38,900
Pretty elaborate trick.

123
00:08:39,274 --> 00:08:42,869
You idiot! It's your fault that
we're going through all this!

124
00:08:43,111 --> 00:08:44,408
What did you say?!

125
00:08:45,147 --> 00:08:46,546
Hey, stop! Stop, I said!

126
00:08:48,784 --> 00:08:50,274
My Ninja tools!

127
00:08:55,190 --> 00:08:57,317
That was an unnecessary help!

128
00:08:57,659 --> 00:08:59,092
Did you say unnecessary?!

129
00:08:59,327 --> 00:09:01,852
Hey bastard, can't you even
thank us for saving you?!

130
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:04,389
You saved me
because it's your duty!

131
00:09:05,033 --> 00:09:06,694
No need to thank you!

132
00:09:07,002 --> 00:09:08,264
What did you say?!

133
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:11,166
Stop, Naruto. He's right.

134
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:16,677
But if you don't want to die,
you should stay close to us.

135
00:09:17,913 --> 00:09:19,574
Hey, where are you going?!

136
00:09:20,015 --> 00:09:21,846
Aren't you going back
to Port Degarashi?

137
00:09:22,717 --> 00:09:25,413
Stupid, I'm heading north from here!

138
00:09:25,787 --> 00:09:28,813
North? Is it faster that way?

139
00:09:29,925 --> 00:09:30,619
Yeah...

140
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:34,686
Who knows...
I really don't trust this guy!

141
00:09:35,497 --> 00:09:37,226
This is why Ninja are no good.

142
00:09:37,432 --> 00:09:38,126
What?!

143
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,031
At this time of year,

144
00:09:40,435 --> 00:09:43,199
a strong seasonal wind blows
across this ocean...

145
00:09:44,372 --> 00:09:47,205
At the starting point, I watched the clouds
and realized it...

146
00:09:48,143 --> 00:09:50,407
That the wind was coming.

147
00:09:51,446 --> 00:09:53,107
On top of that,
at the port to the north,

148
00:09:53,181 --> 00:09:55,445
there's an ocean current
that flows straight to Nagi Island.

149
00:09:56,751 --> 00:10:00,084
This part is different from you guys.
Right here!

150
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:10,254
Looks like it's getting a bit rough.

151
00:10:18,974 --> 00:10:20,464
Hey, don't push it!

152
00:10:20,842 --> 00:10:22,400
Head more towards the south!

153
00:10:22,711 --> 00:10:24,679
But that'll take up quite some time.

154
00:10:24,946 --> 00:10:28,006
Once we get on the land,
no one can run faster than I can.

155
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:30,177
My victory is already set!

156
00:10:30,519 --> 00:10:31,383
All right...

157
00:10:37,792 --> 00:10:39,521
I taste salt in the air.

158
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:42,758
It's the ocean!

159
00:10:49,871 --> 00:10:51,429
What is it that far out on the ocean?

160
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:55,137
It's the halfway point
Nagi Island where Modoroki shrine is.

161
00:11:01,917 --> 00:11:05,853
I can get there within an hour.
Wait for a sec.

162
00:11:09,858 --> 00:11:12,884
Hey, old man, I'm here!
It's Idate from the Wasabi Family!

163
00:11:13,795 --> 00:11:15,194
Ah, I've been waiting for you.

164
00:11:15,931 --> 00:11:17,796
Looks like I was right.

165
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:20,396
I'll need you to lend me a boat.

166
00:11:20,835 --> 00:11:22,928
I see. I have it ready.

167
00:11:23,638 --> 00:11:24,798
Use that boat.

168
00:11:28,443 --> 00:11:30,377
It's the fastest boat around here.

169
00:11:30,779 --> 00:11:31,677
I'm grateful to you!

170
00:11:32,047 --> 00:11:35,847
No problem. Boss Jirocho has done
so much for me.

171
00:11:36,651 --> 00:11:39,085
So, don't lose to Wagarashi!

172
00:11:39,888 --> 00:11:42,880
I'm fed up with how
they handle things.

173
00:11:43,391 --> 00:11:44,688
Leave it to me!

174
00:11:45,126 --> 00:11:46,320
I may be down on my luck now,

175
00:11:46,394 --> 00:11:49,022
but I'm Idate, the number one
henchman of the Wasabi Family!

176
00:11:49,431 --> 00:11:52,127
Rest easy and leave it all to me!

177
00:11:52,734 --> 00:11:54,759
Yeah, right.

178
00:12:14,957 --> 00:12:17,619
<i>We should start seeing</i>
<i>Nagi Island's port soon.</i>

179
00:12:18,527 --> 00:12:20,392
<i>I hope we can get there</i>
<i>before Fukusuke.</i>

180
00:12:29,672 --> 00:12:31,537
Hey, Naruto...
What do you think?

181
00:12:32,074 --> 00:12:33,473
Hm? What about?

182
00:12:33,943 --> 00:12:35,205
That Idate...

183
00:12:36,245 --> 00:12:38,008
He's definitely not
an ordinary man.

184
00:12:42,752 --> 00:12:45,118
He can run extraordinarily fast.

185
00:12:45,821 --> 00:12:48,517
He could have received
special training...

186
00:12:49,592 --> 00:12:50,991
What kind of training?

187
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:54,324
Like, maybe he'd been
in a hidden village.

188
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:59,228
A guy that stupid can't be a Ninja!

189
00:12:59,669 --> 00:13:03,400
Who's talking here?!
You're as stupid as he is!

190
00:13:04,273 --> 00:13:06,138
B-But...

191
00:13:06,409 --> 00:13:09,310
I made it to the final round
of the Chunin Exam!

192
00:13:10,179 --> 00:13:12,647
You were in the final round
of the Chunin Exam?!

193
00:13:12,848 --> 00:13:13,974
Yeah, that's right!

194
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,742
If I weren't interrupted
in the middle of it,

195
00:13:15,818 --> 00:13:18,753
I could have won the tournament
and become a Chunin!

196
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:21,781
Hah!

197
00:13:21,857 --> 00:13:24,951
Then you must have had
a darn easy proctor.

198
00:13:26,462 --> 00:13:29,659
Really, the level of
the Chunin Exam has dropped...

199
00:13:30,132 --> 00:13:30,621
Oh!

200
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:33,368
Idate, so you are...

201
00:13:35,738 --> 00:13:36,932
I remember now!

202
00:13:37,606 --> 00:13:38,573
Idate Morino.

203
00:13:39,442 --> 00:13:41,239
Morino... That's right!

204
00:13:41,811 --> 00:13:43,972
Wasn't the proctor
of the first test...?

205
00:13:44,213 --> 00:13:47,410
<i>Be quiet, you rotten runts!</i>

206
00:13:50,119 --> 00:13:51,381
<i>Sorry to have kept you waiting.</i>

207
00:13:52,121 --> 00:13:56,023
<i>I'm the proctor for</i>
<i>the first test of the Chunin Exam.</i>

208
00:13:56,592 --> 00:13:58,059
<i>My name is Morino lbiki.</i>

209
00:13:58,928 --> 00:14:00,520
Morino... Ibiki...

210
00:14:01,163 --> 00:14:02,061
What did you say?

211
00:14:02,665 --> 00:14:04,997
Brother l-Ibiki is alive?!

212
00:14:05,735 --> 00:14:06,258
Yes...

213
00:14:06,602 --> 00:14:08,593
Of course, he's alive!

214
00:14:08,671 --> 00:14:12,004
He gave me a weird problem
on the 10th question...

215
00:14:12,241 --> 00:14:14,175
Is that true?
He really is alive?!

216
00:14:16,245 --> 00:14:17,803
Wh-What's this?!

217
00:14:18,581 --> 00:14:19,570
An ambush!

218
00:14:27,857 --> 00:14:28,516
How is it?

219
00:14:29,225 --> 00:14:31,523
As you can see,
it's right in front of us.

220
00:14:31,894 --> 00:14:33,828
Then, let's get started
on our plan!

221
00:14:48,978 --> 00:14:49,535
Darn!

222
00:14:51,147 --> 00:14:53,115
Naruto and I will chase them away!

223
00:14:53,749 --> 00:14:55,614
Sakura, take care of Idate!

224
00:14:55,818 --> 00:14:57,115
Isn't it better to run...?

225
00:14:57,319 --> 00:14:58,251
Too late for that!

226
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:06,953
I'll cover you. Remove the ropes!

227
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:08,289
Gotcha!

228
00:15:08,964 --> 00:15:10,693
Darn! I have to cut these!

229
00:15:16,705 --> 00:15:19,401
Darn it! I lost them all that time!

230
00:15:19,975 --> 00:15:21,169
Hey, lend me that thing

231
00:15:22,077 --> 00:15:22,736
What?!

232
00:15:22,812 --> 00:15:24,575
Just hand it to me, hurry!

233
00:15:25,681 --> 00:15:28,582
Bastard, this is more important
than my life.

234
00:15:29,118 --> 00:15:30,585
There's no way
I'll let you use it...

235
00:15:30,786 --> 00:15:33,880
This is no time to be saying
stuff like that!

236
00:15:34,056 --> 00:15:35,353
S-Stop you idiot!

237
00:15:37,026 --> 00:15:38,493
Hurry up, you loser!

238
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:46,126
Heh, piece of cake!

239
00:15:49,371 --> 00:15:52,204
Sakura! They are just clones!

240
00:15:52,641 --> 00:15:56,168
Only the real one can attack you,
so don't worry!

241
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:58,944
<i>Sharingan!</i>

242
00:16:03,519 --> 00:16:04,611
Sakura, Naruto!

243
00:16:04,787 --> 00:16:07,915
The real ones are hiding among
the clones! Be careful!

244
00:16:08,490 --> 00:16:10,219
Sasuke! Guide us!

245
00:16:10,926 --> 00:16:12,826
Idate, stay close to me!

246
00:16:13,229 --> 00:16:15,857
Hah! I don't want a Ninja's help!

247
00:16:16,098 --> 00:16:18,931
Are you still saying that
in this situation?!

248
00:16:19,301 --> 00:16:20,359
Naruto! Behind you!

249
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:25,031
Naruto!

250
00:16:28,978 --> 00:16:29,637
A clone?!

251
00:16:30,012 --> 00:16:30,603
Oh, shoot!

252
00:16:30,980 --> 00:16:33,244
- Clone for clone!
- Clone for clone!

253
00:16:36,518 --> 00:16:38,452
Damn, they got away.

254
00:16:38,687 --> 00:16:39,676
Nice work! Naruto!

255
00:16:40,456 --> 00:16:42,981
That Shadow Clone kid
is troublesome.

256
00:16:43,659 --> 00:16:45,126
The next plan, Kagari!

257
00:16:45,794 --> 00:16:48,126
We'll kill them all!

258
00:16:50,165 --> 00:16:52,190
Water Style!
Black Rain Jutsu!

259
00:16:55,170 --> 00:16:57,695
Sasuke! They've changed
into Water Clones!

260
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:00,273
I know!

261
00:17:06,649 --> 00:17:07,343
Rain?

262
00:17:09,585 --> 00:17:11,212
No! This is oil!

263
00:17:12,621 --> 00:17:15,089
<i>How annoying!</i>
<i>I'll get rid of them all at once!</i>

264
00:17:15,724 --> 00:17:17,157
<i>That's Tiger Seal!</i>

265
00:17:17,693 --> 00:17:19,024
Sasuke, no!

266
00:17:22,364 --> 00:17:23,194
Oops...

267
00:17:24,466 --> 00:17:25,865
Unlucky...

268
00:17:27,736 --> 00:17:29,363
Humph, not really.

269
00:17:32,508 --> 00:17:33,304
Fire attack?!

270
00:17:53,295 --> 00:17:54,023
<i>B-Brother...</i>

271
00:17:55,130 --> 00:17:57,428
<i>Go! Having you stay will be</i>
<i>a burden to me!</i>

272
00:17:59,668 --> 00:18:00,498
B-Brother...

273
00:18:02,771 --> 00:18:03,362
Idate?

274
00:18:04,206 --> 00:18:06,003
N-Nothing

275
00:18:06,542 --> 00:18:08,100
Sasuke, what can we do?!

276
00:18:08,344 --> 00:18:09,834
If the fire is this strong...

277
00:18:12,982 --> 00:18:14,347
We'll have to dive in
to the ocean!

278
00:18:14,883 --> 00:18:17,181
From here, we can swim
to the port of Nagi Island!

279
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,415
Right! There's no other option left.

280
00:18:19,822 --> 00:18:20,982
Idate, can you swim?

281
00:18:21,557 --> 00:18:22,546
Y-Yeah...

282
00:18:27,363 --> 00:18:30,059
Hurry! I'll cover you, so go first!

283
00:18:30,532 --> 00:18:33,501
This smoke should help you
escape unnoticed!

284
00:18:35,004 --> 00:18:35,663
Idate?!

285
00:18:35,738 --> 00:18:36,864
There's no way!

286
00:18:37,039 --> 00:18:37,733
Wha?

287
00:18:38,073 --> 00:18:41,736
You are tricking me into
becoming a decoy!

288
00:18:41,977 --> 00:18:43,069
What are you talking about?!

289
00:18:43,512 --> 00:18:46,242
You're trying to get
the enemy's attention to me!

290
00:18:46,849 --> 00:18:48,077
That's nonsense!

291
00:18:48,183 --> 00:18:50,242
No! I don't trust Ninja!

292
00:18:50,519 --> 00:18:51,486
What are you doing? Go!

293
00:18:51,954 --> 00:18:53,581
Having you stay will be
a burden to us!

294
00:18:58,427 --> 00:19:00,622
<i>Go! Having you stay</i>
<i>is a burden!</i>

295
00:19:02,664 --> 00:19:04,063
Hurry up and go

296
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,528
There's no way we will
use you as a decoy!

297
00:19:09,138 --> 00:19:10,332
N-No...

298
00:19:17,413 --> 00:19:19,040
Cha!

299
00:19:22,451 --> 00:19:23,748
Idate! Duck down!

300
00:19:33,028 --> 00:19:35,895
Trust me Idate!
I promise I'll protect you!

301
00:19:40,035 --> 00:19:40,967
Watch out!

302
00:19:43,839 --> 00:19:44,396
Sa...!

303
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:45,970
Sakura!

304
00:19:46,542 --> 00:19:48,203
S-Sakura...

305
00:19:48,677 --> 00:19:49,803
Go on ahead...

306
00:19:50,946 --> 00:19:52,777
We'll follow you right after!

307
00:19:53,715 --> 00:19:55,307
A-All right...

308
00:20:01,423 --> 00:20:03,186
Well, shall we withdraw now?

309
00:20:05,027 --> 00:20:06,016
Withdraw?

310
00:20:06,628 --> 00:20:09,654
The most enjoyable part
is still left undone.

311
00:20:12,734 --> 00:20:15,032
Darn, they are
unexpectedly tenacious.

312
00:20:15,471 --> 00:20:19,066
Yeah. But we won't
let them get away.

313
00:20:37,126 --> 00:20:39,026
I-I should be okay here...

314
00:20:49,004 --> 00:20:51,302
Long time no see, Idate.

315
00:20:51,707 --> 00:20:53,140
Y-You are...

316
00:20:55,477 --> 00:20:59,072
I have taught you so many times
not to trust anyone.

317
00:21:01,316 --> 00:21:03,580
Such a fool, you are...

318
00:21:06,755 --> 00:21:11,454
<i>I believe your promise,</i>
<i>its a true heart give me courage</i>

319
00:21:11,527 --> 00:21:15,861
<i>Always I feel it</i>
<i>the precious time with you</i>

320
00:21:16,465 --> 00:21:19,992
<i>On your still shoulder</i>

321
00:21:21,236 --> 00:21:25,696
<i>I feel the wind that blows</i>
<i>towards tomorrow</i>

322
00:21:25,874 --> 00:21:31,312
<i>The city lights are like pieces of stars</i>

323
00:21:31,813 --> 00:21:36,113
<i>That hold us together</i>

324
00:21:36,585 --> 00:21:45,823
<i>"Each one of us glows differently,"</i>

325
00:21:45,894 --> 00:21:48,488
<i>you say laughingly</i>

326
00:21:48,730 --> 00:21:54,396
<i>but you look most dazzling</i>

327
00:21:54,970 --> 00:21:59,339
<i>Like a comet,</i>

328
00:21:59,408 --> 00:22:05,506
<i>like the rainbow after the storm</i>

329
00:22:05,581 --> 00:22:12,680
<i>You bring light into my heart</i>

330
00:22:13,689 --> 00:22:23,064
<i>Being lost can be the answer</i>

331
00:22:24,399 --> 00:22:31,931
<i>Let's promise we won't cheat</i>

332
00:22:32,007 --> 00:22:36,000
<i>Uh...like a shooting star,</i>
<i>we do go ahead.</i>

333
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:42,514
Fool or whatever...
It doesn't matter now how you used to be.

334
00:22:42,884 --> 00:22:45,375
This race is not over yet!

335
00:22:45,721 --> 00:22:49,122
You'll never know unless
you try'til the very end!

336
00:22:49,658 --> 00:22:51,956
Boss Jirocho believes in you.

337
00:22:52,261 --> 00:22:57,824
If you have time to stall and act cool,
why don't you show some guts?!

338
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:02,727
Next time: "Run Idate Run!
Nagi Island Awaits!"
